1
00:00:00,968 --> 00:00:04,037
Enter the battle
and lead the way.

2
00:00:04,037 --> 00:00:06,039
Ride, King of Knights, Alfred!

3
00:00:06,039 --> 00:00:10,477
♪

4
00:00:10,477 --> 00:00:13,247
And I call Blaster
Blade to the rear guard.

5
00:00:13,247 --> 00:00:34,401
♪

6
00:00:34,401 --> 00:00:37,804
Final turn.

7
00:00:37,804 --> 00:00:38,772
We're not done yet.

8
00:00:38,772 --> 00:00:50,484
♪

9
00:00:50,484 --> 00:00:53,687
(screaming)

10
00:00:53,687 --> 00:00:58,258
♪

11
00:00:58,258 --> 00:01:00,294
I used up my entire
hand to defend it

12
00:01:00,294 --> 00:01:01,495
and it still wasn't enough.

13
00:01:01,495 --> 00:01:06,700
♪

14
00:01:06,700 --> 00:01:09,503
Our first player moving on
to the championship match

15
00:01:09,503 --> 00:01:11,138
is Toshiki Kai!

16
00:01:11,138 --> 00:01:14,875
(cheers and applause)

17
00:01:14,875 --> 00:01:17,611
Kai won his match.

18
00:01:17,611 --> 00:01:19,179
Kai.

19
00:01:19,179 --> 00:01:21,682
♪

20
00:02:45,198 --> 00:02:48,600
♪

21
00:02:55,208 --> 00:02:56,843
That was so fast.

22
00:02:56,843 --> 00:02:58,578
Can you believe that match?

23
00:02:58,578 --> 00:03:00,747
I've seen him finish
quickly before...

24
00:03:00,747 --> 00:03:03,350
Looks like you made
it to the final round.

25
00:03:03,350 --> 00:03:05,419
Hm.

26
00:03:05,419 --> 00:03:07,921
Was there ever any doubt?

27
00:03:10,090 --> 00:03:11,525
That settles it.

28
00:03:11,525 --> 00:03:12,793
The winner of this battle

29
00:03:12,793 --> 00:03:16,163
is moving on to fight
Kai for the championship.

30
00:03:16,163 --> 00:03:18,331
I'm gonna take this.

31
00:03:18,331 --> 00:03:25,305
♪

32
00:03:25,305 --> 00:03:27,307
I know Aichi really
wants to battle Kai,

33
00:03:27,307 --> 00:03:30,844
but I can't lose
in front of Emi.

34
00:03:30,844 --> 00:03:33,547
♪

35
00:03:33,547 --> 00:03:34,815
Sorry, Aichi.

36
00:03:34,815 --> 00:03:37,551
You're going down.

37
00:03:37,551 --> 00:03:38,852
It's my turn.

38
00:03:38,852 --> 00:03:41,855
And he's already at four damage.

39
00:03:41,855 --> 00:03:44,524
♪

40
00:03:44,524 --> 00:03:46,626
I've gotta find a way to
get my attacks through.

41
00:03:46,626 --> 00:03:50,831
♪

42
00:03:50,831 --> 00:03:52,666
Here I come, Kamui.

43
00:03:52,666 --> 00:03:58,371
♪

44
00:03:58,371 --> 00:04:01,675
First I'll switch the
positions of Marron and Epona

45
00:04:01,675 --> 00:04:03,944
to make way for Gancelot.

46
00:04:03,944 --> 00:04:07,781
♪

47
00:04:07,781 --> 00:04:10,784
Now I'll have
Wingal replace Flogal.

48
00:04:10,784 --> 00:04:12,319
He's shifting around
his battle formation

49
00:04:12,319 --> 00:04:14,054
to increase attack power.

50
00:04:14,054 --> 00:04:16,490
This is the most
important moment of the game.

51
00:04:16,490 --> 00:04:18,759
I'll defend with
everything I got.

52
00:04:18,759 --> 00:04:20,026
With support from Wingal

53
00:04:20,026 --> 00:04:22,796
I increase the power
of Blaster Blade.

54
00:04:22,796 --> 00:04:23,997
He's attacking your Vanguard,

55
00:04:23,997 --> 00:04:25,699
Mr. Invincible.

56
00:04:25,699 --> 00:04:27,434
Thanks to Wingal's support skill

57
00:04:27,434 --> 00:04:29,803
he gets an
additional 4,000 power.

58
00:04:29,803 --> 00:04:34,107
♪

59
00:04:34,107 --> 00:04:36,576
I'll let that one through.

60
00:04:36,576 --> 00:04:38,378
But that would be
really easy to guard.

61
00:04:38,378 --> 00:04:40,380
Does this mean
he's giving up, yo?

62
00:04:40,380 --> 00:04:44,184
♪

63
00:04:44,184 --> 00:04:45,585
Damage trigger check.

64
00:04:45,585 --> 00:04:46,987
Yes, I got one.

65
00:04:46,987 --> 00:04:51,158
That's an extra 5,000
power going to my Vanguard.

66
00:04:51,158 --> 00:04:53,059
And I return my
rear guard Invincible

67
00:04:53,059 --> 00:04:54,961
to the standing position.

68
00:04:54,961 --> 00:04:56,062
Power boost or not,

69
00:04:56,062 --> 00:04:58,765
I'm attacking Mr.
Invincible with Alfred.

70
00:04:58,765 --> 00:04:59,933
Royal Paladins,

71
00:04:59,933 --> 00:05:03,069
it's time to lend
your power to the king.

72
00:05:03,069 --> 00:05:08,208
♪

73
00:05:08,208 --> 00:05:10,844
I guard with Shining Lady.

74
00:05:10,844 --> 00:05:13,413
♪

75
00:05:13,413 --> 00:05:14,614
Well, that should do it.

76
00:05:14,614 --> 00:05:16,583
A damage field on top
of the trigger effect

77
00:05:16,583 --> 00:05:18,385
he just gave to his Vanguard.

78
00:05:18,385 --> 00:05:20,153
Looks like this attack

79
00:05:20,153 --> 00:05:22,355
isn't gonna be strong enough.

80
00:05:22,355 --> 00:05:24,291
I guard with Rock the Wall, too.

81
00:05:24,291 --> 00:05:25,392
Huh?

82
00:05:25,392 --> 00:05:27,494
Hey, what was the
point of doing that?

83
00:05:27,494 --> 00:05:29,830
He just wasted
another defense card.

84
00:05:29,830 --> 00:05:34,167
Actually, you can't
be so sure of that.

85
00:05:34,167 --> 00:05:35,635
My twin drive.

86
00:05:35,635 --> 00:05:36,570
First check.

87
00:05:36,570 --> 00:05:39,940
♪

88
00:05:39,940 --> 00:05:41,942
Second check.

89
00:05:41,942 --> 00:05:44,010
All right, a critical trigger.

90
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:45,345
Huh?

91
00:05:45,345 --> 00:05:46,446
With a double shield

92
00:05:46,446 --> 00:05:49,616
this attack isn't
going anywhere.

93
00:05:49,616 --> 00:05:50,917
What's he gonna do?

94
00:05:50,917 --> 00:05:53,286
So Aichi was able to
get a critical trigger,

95
00:05:53,286 --> 00:05:54,487
but it's not gonna help him?

96
00:05:54,487 --> 00:05:56,456
Looks like Kamui planned ahead.

97
00:05:56,456 --> 00:05:57,824
He used two cards to guard

98
00:05:57,824 --> 00:05:59,926
because he knew
this could happen.

99
00:05:59,926 --> 00:06:02,395
Hm.

100
00:06:02,395 --> 00:06:03,530
Hmm.

101
00:06:03,530 --> 00:06:05,866
I won't let this
chance go to waste.

102
00:06:05,866 --> 00:06:08,101
Activating critical trigger

103
00:06:08,101 --> 00:06:10,670
giving all effects to
Solitary Knight, Gancelot.

104
00:06:10,670 --> 00:06:13,273
♪

105
00:06:13,273 --> 00:06:16,209
I just need to deal
one more damage to him.

106
00:06:16,209 --> 00:06:18,778
It all comes down
to this attack.

107
00:06:18,778 --> 00:06:21,448
I'm gonna move Shining
Lady over to the drop zone.

108
00:06:21,448 --> 00:06:23,049
Rock the Wall's defense skill

109
00:06:23,049 --> 00:06:26,086
sends him to the
soul after guarding.

110
00:06:26,086 --> 00:06:28,822
That makes five
cards in the soul.

111
00:06:28,822 --> 00:06:30,857
I attack your
Vanguard with Gancelot

112
00:06:30,857 --> 00:06:32,292
supported by Marron.

113
00:06:32,292 --> 00:06:35,428
♪

114
00:06:35,428 --> 00:06:37,464
With only two cards in hand

115
00:06:37,464 --> 00:06:40,433
he might not have
anything left to defend with.

116
00:06:40,433 --> 00:06:42,969
I guard the attack
with Rock the Wall.

117
00:06:42,969 --> 00:06:52,979
♪

118
00:06:52,979 --> 00:06:56,416
I move this card to
the soul stack as well.

119
00:06:56,416 --> 00:06:58,084
I gave it everything I could,

120
00:06:58,084 --> 00:07:00,287
but it wasn't enough.

121
00:07:00,287 --> 00:07:03,657
I was so close to ending it.

122
00:07:03,657 --> 00:07:06,359
Hey, can I ask you
something about Rock the Wall?

123
00:07:06,359 --> 00:07:08,094
Don't cards usually
go to the drop zone

124
00:07:08,094 --> 00:07:10,030
after they guard an attack?

125
00:07:10,030 --> 00:07:11,298
Not that card.

126
00:07:11,298 --> 00:07:13,566
Its ability allows you
to place it into the soul

127
00:07:13,566 --> 00:07:15,769
instead of sending it
up to the drop zone.

128
00:07:15,769 --> 00:07:16,603
Ah.

129
00:07:16,603 --> 00:07:17,804
Now that I think of it,

130
00:07:17,804 --> 00:07:20,407
Kamui's soul must
be pretty big by now.

131
00:07:20,407 --> 00:07:22,809
I stand and draw.

132
00:07:22,809 --> 00:07:24,210
Listen up, Aichi.

133
00:07:24,210 --> 00:07:25,378
It's been fun so far,

134
00:07:25,378 --> 00:07:28,548
but we need to bring
this game to an end.

135
00:07:28,548 --> 00:07:30,750
I can't let him do that.

136
00:07:30,750 --> 00:07:33,320
Hit me with your best shot.

137
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:34,621
Here goes.

138
00:07:34,621 --> 00:07:37,857
I ride Invincible
on top of Invincible.

139
00:07:37,857 --> 00:07:38,758
Huh?

140
00:07:38,758 --> 00:07:42,829
♪

141
00:07:42,829 --> 00:07:44,698
Now that seems like
a waste of a card.

142
00:07:44,698 --> 00:07:47,400
Hm.

143
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:49,836
What was the point of that?

144
00:07:49,836 --> 00:07:53,606
And now I soul charge
using Invincible's skill.

145
00:07:53,606 --> 00:07:56,209
That makes eight
cards in the soul.

146
00:07:56,209 --> 00:07:59,179
However, I haven't flipped
any cards in the damage zone

147
00:07:59,179 --> 00:08:02,148
so there are no
abilities activated.

148
00:08:02,148 --> 00:08:04,184
He just wasted another card.

149
00:08:04,184 --> 00:08:06,920
What's he up to?

150
00:08:06,920 --> 00:08:08,321
Calling King of Sword.

151
00:08:08,321 --> 00:08:11,358
♪

152
00:08:11,358 --> 00:08:13,293
I'm coming at ya, bro.

153
00:08:13,293 --> 00:08:16,896
I'll have the King of
Sword attack Alfred.

154
00:08:16,896 --> 00:08:18,565
I have to let this one through.

155
00:08:18,565 --> 00:08:22,635
♪

156
00:08:22,635 --> 00:08:25,071
Checking for a damage trigger.

157
00:08:25,071 --> 00:08:26,573
He has two more attacks

158
00:08:26,573 --> 00:08:28,208
and I have two defense cards.

159
00:08:28,208 --> 00:08:29,442
I can do this.

160
00:08:29,442 --> 00:08:31,111
With the support of Shining Lady

161
00:08:31,111 --> 00:08:32,879
I attack your Vanguard again.

162
00:08:32,879 --> 00:08:35,181
Let's go, Invincible!

163
00:08:35,181 --> 00:08:37,817
♪

164
00:08:37,817 --> 00:08:40,620
I guard that with Llew!

165
00:08:40,620 --> 00:08:48,161
♪

166
00:08:48,161 --> 00:08:49,295
Okay.

167
00:08:49,295 --> 00:08:51,531
Here comes the last one.

168
00:08:51,531 --> 00:08:53,299
Using Lucky Girl as support

169
00:08:53,299 --> 00:08:55,168
I attack Alfred
with my Vanguard.

170
00:08:55,168 --> 00:08:58,705
♪

171
00:08:58,705 --> 00:09:00,273
I guard with Morgana.

172
00:09:00,273 --> 00:09:01,641
Joining the defense

173
00:09:01,641 --> 00:09:04,778
I intercept with Blaster Blade.

174
00:09:04,778 --> 00:09:06,579
♪

175
00:09:06,579 --> 00:09:08,748
Hm, here we go.

176
00:09:08,748 --> 00:09:09,849
First check.

177
00:09:09,849 --> 00:09:11,651
He has to pull a
drive trigger here

178
00:09:11,651 --> 00:09:14,687
or the turn passes back to me.

179
00:09:14,687 --> 00:09:16,790
Now the second check.

180
00:09:16,790 --> 00:09:19,659
Stand trigger.

181
00:09:19,659 --> 00:09:21,294
I stand King of Sword.

182
00:09:21,294 --> 00:09:25,331
Plus, I add 5,000
power to my Vanguard.

183
00:09:25,331 --> 00:09:27,000
I guess this is the end.

184
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:32,205
♪

185
00:09:32,205 --> 00:09:33,907
Iron Fist strike!

186
00:09:33,907 --> 00:09:36,376
Ah!

187
00:09:36,376 --> 00:09:38,611
Damage trigger check.

188
00:09:38,611 --> 00:09:41,314
No way, it's a heal trigger!

189
00:09:41,314 --> 00:09:44,984
I use its effect to raise
Alfred's power by 5,000.

190
00:09:44,984 --> 00:09:48,955
And I recover one damage.

191
00:09:48,955 --> 00:09:50,090
I did it.

192
00:09:50,090 --> 00:09:54,094
I was able to
survive all his attacks.

193
00:09:54,094 --> 00:09:55,628
There's something
you should know, Aichi.

194
00:09:55,628 --> 00:09:56,729
Huh?

195
00:09:56,729 --> 00:10:00,567
My Vanguard soul has
eight cards in it.

196
00:10:00,567 --> 00:10:02,235
A soul blast?

197
00:10:02,235 --> 00:10:06,539
♪

198
00:10:09,442 --> 00:10:15,548
♪

199
00:10:15,548 --> 00:10:17,417
My soul blast.

200
00:10:17,417 --> 00:10:18,852
What does it do?

201
00:10:18,852 --> 00:10:22,522
I move eight cards from
my soul into the drop zone.

202
00:10:22,522 --> 00:10:26,259
Next I pay a cost of
five from the damage zone.

203
00:10:26,259 --> 00:10:28,361
Activating
Invincible's final skill

204
00:10:28,361 --> 00:10:30,797
I'll have all my units
stand up once more.

205
00:10:30,797 --> 00:10:32,665
What?

206
00:10:32,665 --> 00:10:42,108
♪

207
00:10:42,108 --> 00:10:43,843
His secret technique?

208
00:10:43,843 --> 00:10:46,179
Tornado stand galactica!

209
00:10:46,179 --> 00:10:50,783
♪

210
00:10:50,783 --> 00:10:52,819
(laughing)

211
00:10:56,122 --> 00:10:59,259
In order for Kamui to activate
Mr. Invincible's soul blast

212
00:10:59,259 --> 00:11:01,027
he had to have eight
cards in the soul

213
00:11:01,027 --> 00:11:03,496
combined with five
unflipped damage as well.

214
00:11:03,496 --> 00:11:05,098
And you can only use that move

215
00:11:05,098 --> 00:11:07,100
after your Vanguard
lands a damaging attack

216
00:11:07,100 --> 00:11:08,501
on your opponent.

217
00:11:08,501 --> 00:11:09,903
Huh, I see.

218
00:11:09,903 --> 00:11:11,971
That explains why he's
been sending so many cards

219
00:11:11,971 --> 00:11:13,339
to the soul recently.

220
00:11:13,339 --> 00:11:15,542
Oh, yeah, you're right.

221
00:11:15,542 --> 00:11:18,711
He's been preparing for
this moment the entire game.

222
00:11:18,711 --> 00:11:20,413
Exciting.

223
00:11:20,413 --> 00:11:23,049
♪

224
00:11:23,049 --> 00:11:25,885
All of his units
are ready to attack?

225
00:11:25,885 --> 00:11:27,820
This is the end, bro.

226
00:11:27,820 --> 00:11:29,055
Now you know

227
00:11:29,055 --> 00:11:31,858
the power of my Nova Grapplers.

228
00:11:31,858 --> 00:11:33,459
With the support of Lucky Girl

229
00:11:33,459 --> 00:11:36,029
I'll have Invincible
attack your Vanguard.

230
00:11:36,029 --> 00:11:45,438
♪

231
00:11:45,438 --> 00:11:49,475
There's nothing I
can do to stop you.

232
00:11:49,475 --> 00:11:52,111
♪

233
00:11:52,111 --> 00:11:54,214
Twin drive, first check,

234
00:11:54,214 --> 00:11:56,249
second check.

235
00:11:56,249 --> 00:12:01,221
♪

236
00:12:01,221 --> 00:12:02,355
Iron fist strike!

237
00:12:02,355 --> 00:12:06,259
♪

238
00:12:07,794 --> 00:12:11,397
I do a damage trigger check.

239
00:12:11,397 --> 00:12:14,934
♪

240
00:12:14,934 --> 00:12:16,803
I lost the game.

241
00:12:16,803 --> 00:12:19,939
♪

242
00:12:19,939 --> 00:12:21,274
Kai.

243
00:12:21,274 --> 00:12:24,410
Looks like I just wasn't
strong enough after all.

244
00:12:24,410 --> 00:12:26,346
And there you
have it, everybody.

245
00:12:26,346 --> 00:12:29,749
The winner is Kamui Katsuragi.

246
00:12:29,749 --> 00:12:33,086
Oh, yeah!

247
00:12:33,086 --> 00:12:34,854
Aichi.

248
00:12:34,854 --> 00:12:37,624
I still haven't learned
all the rules of the game.

249
00:12:37,624 --> 00:12:39,993
But I had a lot of
fun watching you play.

250
00:12:39,993 --> 00:12:42,195
So you did great.

251
00:12:42,195 --> 00:12:44,030
Oh, that's sweet, Emi.

252
00:12:44,030 --> 00:12:46,099
She's right, man.

253
00:12:46,099 --> 00:12:48,301
Oh, hey you guys.

254
00:12:48,301 --> 00:12:49,802
That was epic!

255
00:12:49,802 --> 00:12:51,838
Yeah, not bad for a shrimp.

256
00:12:51,838 --> 00:12:52,639
Hey, Aichi.

257
00:12:52,639 --> 00:12:53,840
Huh?

258
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:55,341
You know, you've
gotten so much better

259
00:12:55,341 --> 00:12:57,277
since the last time we battled.

260
00:12:57,277 --> 00:13:00,413
At this rate I don't like
my chances for next time.

261
00:13:00,413 --> 00:13:02,649
We know a crazy strong
player when we see one.

262
00:13:02,649 --> 00:13:04,484
Say yes, yo.

263
00:13:04,484 --> 00:13:05,585
Thanks, you guys.

264
00:13:05,585 --> 00:13:06,786
Hey, you already won,

265
00:13:06,786 --> 00:13:08,254
you don't need to
make fun of him, too.

266
00:13:08,254 --> 00:13:10,323
It's not what
you think, Morikawa.

267
00:13:10,323 --> 00:13:12,191
They're just trying to make
me feel better about losing,

268
00:13:12,191 --> 00:13:13,526
that's all.

269
00:13:13,526 --> 00:13:17,964
And I'm really happy I
got to play in that match.

270
00:13:17,964 --> 00:13:18,865
It was fun,

271
00:13:18,865 --> 00:13:23,236
but losing feels awful.

272
00:13:23,236 --> 00:13:25,638
♪

273
00:13:25,638 --> 00:13:28,641
Aichi.

274
00:13:28,641 --> 00:13:29,175
Hm.

275
00:13:29,175 --> 00:13:30,610
Hey, Kamui.

276
00:13:30,610 --> 00:13:32,879
We'll start the final match
after a short break, okay?

277
00:13:32,879 --> 00:13:34,213
Prepare yourself.

278
00:13:34,213 --> 00:13:35,415
Sure thing.

279
00:13:35,415 --> 00:13:37,417
Hey, you're gonna
watch me, right, Emi?

280
00:13:37,417 --> 00:13:39,652
I'll be champion in no time.

281
00:13:39,652 --> 00:13:42,555
Well, uh...

282
00:13:42,555 --> 00:13:45,124
So, are you ready
for the finals or what?

283
00:13:45,124 --> 00:13:48,628
Of course I a‐‐ oh!

284
00:13:48,628 --> 00:13:49,929
Huh?

285
00:13:49,929 --> 00:13:50,630
You okay?

286
00:13:50,630 --> 00:13:51,964
What happened, yo?

287
00:13:51,964 --> 00:13:54,701
Uh, forget about it.

288
00:13:54,701 --> 00:13:56,869
My legs are feeling
wobbly all of a sudden.

289
00:13:56,869 --> 00:14:00,273
What's going on?

290
00:14:00,273 --> 00:14:05,044
It looks like he does
get nervous after all.

291
00:14:05,044 --> 00:14:07,447
Hm.

292
00:14:07,447 --> 00:14:20,193
♪

293
00:14:20,193 --> 00:14:22,462
Did you have fun today?

294
00:14:22,462 --> 00:14:23,663
Not really.

295
00:14:23,663 --> 00:14:25,031
I wouldn't have
entered this tournament

296
00:14:25,031 --> 00:14:26,065
if you hadn't forced me to.

297
00:14:26,065 --> 00:14:34,907
♪

298
00:14:34,907 --> 00:14:37,877
You know Kai is obviously
gonna win the championship.

299
00:14:37,877 --> 00:14:39,078
No way, dude.

300
00:14:39,078 --> 00:14:41,247
Kamui's the best ever.

301
00:14:41,247 --> 00:14:42,982
You're not allowed to leave yet.

302
00:14:42,982 --> 00:14:45,351
Wait around until
after the final match.

303
00:14:45,351 --> 00:14:45,852
Huh?

304
00:14:45,852 --> 00:14:47,086
Okay.

305
00:14:47,086 --> 00:14:48,821
For the final we'll
be using the patented

306
00:14:48,821 --> 00:14:51,391
Card Capital standing
fight table, patent pending.

307
00:14:56,396 --> 00:15:01,067
♪

308
00:15:01,067 --> 00:15:02,568
How do you expect
me to battle someone

309
00:15:02,568 --> 00:15:04,504
I can't even look in the eye?

310
00:15:04,504 --> 00:15:06,973
Raise my platform
higher, already!

311
00:15:06,973 --> 00:15:08,441
Well, if I raise it any higher

312
00:15:08,441 --> 00:15:10,810
you'll have trouble
handling your cards.

313
00:15:10,810 --> 00:15:13,146
Kamui, I think you're just
gonna have to put up with it.

314
00:15:13,146 --> 00:15:14,447
That's lame, yo.

315
00:15:14,447 --> 00:15:15,548
Fine then.

316
00:15:15,548 --> 00:15:17,617
I'll play at a
height disadvantage.

317
00:15:17,617 --> 00:15:20,653
But I'm not happy about this!

318
00:15:23,589 --> 00:15:24,991
Aichi.

319
00:15:24,991 --> 00:15:26,025
Now then.

320
00:15:26,025 --> 00:15:27,493
The time has finally come

321
00:15:27,493 --> 00:15:31,230
for the Card Capital Shop
Tournament Championship Match!

322
00:15:31,230 --> 00:15:32,398
Toshiki Kai

323
00:15:32,398 --> 00:15:35,001
versus Kamui Katsuragi.

324
00:15:35,001 --> 00:15:37,670
I've been waiting for
my chance at a rematch.

325
00:15:37,670 --> 00:15:39,972
But this time I, uh,

326
00:15:39,972 --> 00:15:41,841
I'm gonna have my reform.

327
00:15:41,841 --> 00:15:43,443
He means "revenge".

328
00:15:43,443 --> 00:15:46,245
That didn't make sense.

329
00:15:46,245 --> 00:15:47,380
It's too bad

330
00:15:47,380 --> 00:15:49,081
that I have to face you again.

331
00:15:49,081 --> 00:15:51,150
What?

332
00:15:51,150 --> 00:15:52,285
I was hoping I'd be able to play

333
00:15:52,285 --> 00:15:53,786
someone worthwhile
in the finals,

334
00:15:53,786 --> 00:15:56,022
but it seems I was dreaming.

335
00:15:56,022 --> 00:15:59,058
I'll show you.

336
00:15:59,058 --> 00:16:01,928
Hey, what are you
doing over here?

337
00:16:01,928 --> 00:16:03,296
Huh?

338
00:16:03,296 --> 00:16:05,298
Are you still
upset about losing?

339
00:16:05,298 --> 00:16:06,165
Look.

340
00:16:06,165 --> 00:16:07,967
I'm a bit of an expert.

341
00:16:07,967 --> 00:16:10,203
When you lose you're not
allowed to give up, okay?

342
00:16:10,203 --> 00:16:11,571
You're an expert?

343
00:16:11,571 --> 00:16:13,639
On losing, yeah.

344
00:16:13,639 --> 00:16:15,074
I needed that.

345
00:16:15,074 --> 00:16:16,342
Thanks, guys.

346
00:16:16,342 --> 00:16:18,077
Stand up, my Vanguard.

347
00:16:18,077 --> 00:16:20,046
Stand up, the Vanguard.

348
00:16:20,046 --> 00:16:21,280
The main event.

349
00:16:21,280 --> 00:16:23,349
Come on, let's go watch.

350
00:16:23,349 --> 00:16:25,218
Sure.

351
00:16:25,218 --> 00:16:29,155
I ride Jarron and call Aermo.

352
00:16:29,155 --> 00:16:30,923
I ride Tough Boy.

353
00:16:35,027 --> 00:16:36,762
♪

354
00:16:36,762 --> 00:16:41,100
Brutal Jack released
into high gear.

355
00:16:41,100 --> 00:16:44,070
I attack you with Brutal Jack.

356
00:16:44,070 --> 00:16:45,505
Your attack will fail.

357
00:16:45,505 --> 00:16:47,440
I guard with Ganlu.

358
00:16:47,440 --> 00:16:55,081
♪

359
00:16:55,081 --> 00:16:56,349
This match.

360
00:16:56,349 --> 00:16:59,919
It's great.

361
00:16:59,919 --> 00:17:02,622
But see how you like
my superior ride.

362
00:17:02,622 --> 00:17:05,992
The embodiment
of victory, Aleph.

363
00:17:05,992 --> 00:17:08,194
♪

364
00:17:08,194 --> 00:17:10,997
Nova Grapplers,
rise to the occasion.

365
00:17:10,997 --> 00:17:12,865
Tornado stand galactica!

366
00:17:12,865 --> 00:17:20,139
♪

367
00:17:20,139 --> 00:17:21,007
That's it.

368
00:17:21,007 --> 00:17:22,909
The move he beat me with.

369
00:17:22,909 --> 00:17:24,777
Let's see if you can withstand

370
00:17:24,777 --> 00:17:26,646
three more of my attacks.

371
00:17:26,646 --> 00:17:28,147
Just you try me.

372
00:17:28,147 --> 00:17:29,415
Oh, yeah?

373
00:17:29,415 --> 00:17:31,984
Such big talk for
a guy about to lose.

374
00:17:31,984 --> 00:17:33,586
With Tough Boy's support,

375
00:17:33,586 --> 00:17:36,289
my Clay‐Doll attacks
your Dragonic Overlord.

376
00:17:36,289 --> 00:17:40,359
♪

377
00:17:40,359 --> 00:17:42,728
Checking the damage trigger.

378
00:17:42,728 --> 00:17:44,096
Supported by Clara,

379
00:17:44,096 --> 00:17:46,198
Mr. Invincible attacks you next.

380
00:17:46,198 --> 00:17:47,199
I'll guard with Tahr,

381
00:17:47,199 --> 00:17:49,101
the Embodiment of Spear.

382
00:17:49,101 --> 00:17:51,537
Kai just stopped
him in his tracks.

383
00:17:51,537 --> 00:17:52,872
There's still more.

384
00:17:52,872 --> 00:17:55,575
I'm sending in
Tough Boy supported by Shout.

385
00:17:55,575 --> 00:17:59,011
I intercept with Nehalem.

386
00:17:59,011 --> 00:18:00,446
I've used too much of my hand,

387
00:18:00,446 --> 00:18:03,549
not to mention my rear
guard holding him off.

388
00:18:03,549 --> 00:18:06,619
My units don't have
the power to finish him.

389
00:18:06,619 --> 00:18:08,688
They're both playing so well.

390
00:18:08,688 --> 00:18:11,591
Kai hardly flinched
stopping all those attacks.

391
00:18:11,591 --> 00:18:13,926
Even after tornado
stand galactica.

392
00:18:13,926 --> 00:18:15,995
I've never seen
anything like it.

393
00:18:15,995 --> 00:18:18,130
This match is at a
whole other level.

394
00:18:18,130 --> 00:18:20,066
Let's put an end to this.

395
00:18:20,066 --> 00:18:21,701
Ah.

396
00:18:21,701 --> 00:18:22,835
Final turn.

397
00:18:22,835 --> 00:18:24,604
Huh?

398
00:18:24,604 --> 00:18:26,739
I can't believe it.

399
00:18:26,739 --> 00:18:28,474
The last battle
of the tournament.

400
00:18:28,474 --> 00:18:31,110
It all comes down to this turn.

401
00:18:31,110 --> 00:18:36,816
♪

402
00:18:36,816 --> 00:18:37,984
Supported by Bahr

403
00:18:37,984 --> 00:18:41,020
I attack Invincible with
my Dragonic Overlord.

404
00:18:41,020 --> 00:18:47,193
♪

405
00:18:47,193 --> 00:18:50,029
Lucky Girl will guard that.

406
00:18:50,029 --> 00:18:51,697
The twin drive.

407
00:18:51,697 --> 00:18:53,899
First check.

408
00:18:53,899 --> 00:18:55,167
Second check.

409
00:18:55,167 --> 00:19:00,072
♪

410
00:19:00,072 --> 00:19:02,708
I got a critical trigger.

411
00:19:02,708 --> 00:19:06,879
Dragonic Overlord
gains 5,000 power.

412
00:19:06,879 --> 00:19:07,980
♪

413
00:19:07,980 --> 00:19:10,750
And I give it the
plus one damage as well.

414
00:19:10,750 --> 00:19:23,396
♪

415
00:19:23,396 --> 00:19:26,198
I need a heal trigger.

416
00:19:26,198 --> 00:19:28,000
♪

417
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:29,835
(shouting)

418
00:19:29,835 --> 00:19:33,039
♪

419
00:19:33,039 --> 00:19:35,274
Now you're finished.

420
00:19:35,274 --> 00:19:39,111
♪

421
00:19:39,111 --> 00:19:39,945
There you have it, folks,

422
00:19:39,945 --> 00:19:41,313
you've seen it yourselves.

423
00:19:41,313 --> 00:19:44,684
The winner is Toshiki Kai.

424
00:19:44,684 --> 00:19:47,186
(applause and cheering)

425
00:19:49,388 --> 00:19:51,057
Amazing.

426
00:19:51,057 --> 00:19:53,993
They're both such
great fighters.

427
00:19:53,993 --> 00:19:58,330
Hopefully I can be
like them one day.

428
00:19:59,665 --> 00:20:01,701
Wait, wait, wait, wait!

429
00:20:01,701 --> 00:20:03,335
The champion has been decided,

430
00:20:03,335 --> 00:20:05,371
but that's not the
only exciting news.

431
00:20:05,371 --> 00:20:07,640
I have a very important
announcement to make.

432
00:20:07,640 --> 00:20:09,909
Huh?

433
00:20:09,909 --> 00:20:11,210
Pardon me.

434
00:20:11,210 --> 00:20:14,246
The Card Capital Shop
Champion, Toshiki Kai,

435
00:20:14,246 --> 00:20:16,515
and our runner up,
Kamui Katsuragi,

436
00:20:16,515 --> 00:20:18,617
will be joined by our
other semi finalists,

437
00:20:18,617 --> 00:20:20,986
Aichi Sendou and Misaki Tokura

438
00:20:20,986 --> 00:20:24,023
as they prepare for this!

439
00:20:24,023 --> 00:20:25,391
Excuse the small poster,

440
00:20:25,391 --> 00:20:27,026
there was a larger version.

441
00:20:27,026 --> 00:20:29,595
But the assist‐i‐cat
had a nap on it.

442
00:20:29,595 --> 00:20:30,596
Whoa.

443
00:20:30,596 --> 00:20:31,464
No way.

444
00:20:31,464 --> 00:20:33,432
Great work, man.

445
00:20:33,432 --> 00:20:34,133
What is it?

446
00:20:34,133 --> 00:20:36,235
Whoa, incredible.

447
00:20:36,235 --> 00:20:39,371
Misaki, you get to compete in
an even bigger card tournament.

448
00:20:39,371 --> 00:20:40,840
Isn't that great?

449
00:20:40,840 --> 00:20:42,007
The National Championship

450
00:20:42,007 --> 00:20:44,376
is our country's biggest
Vanguard tournament.

451
00:20:44,376 --> 00:20:45,811
By making the top four

452
00:20:45,811 --> 00:20:48,214
you've proved that you're
ready to represent Card Capital

453
00:20:48,214 --> 00:20:50,816
on the national level.

454
00:20:50,816 --> 00:20:53,185
First you'll have to compete
in a regional qualifier

455
00:20:53,185 --> 00:20:54,587
on your way to the nationals.

456
00:20:54,587 --> 00:20:55,955
But with players this strong

457
00:20:55,955 --> 00:20:58,023
I have no doubt you'll
win the regionals.

458
00:20:58,023 --> 00:21:00,626
Then you'll compete against
the best in the country

459
00:21:00,626 --> 00:21:03,562
for the title of
National Vanguard Champion.

460
00:21:03,562 --> 00:21:06,031
Now your team can
only have three players,

461
00:21:06,031 --> 00:21:08,000
with one of you
serving as an alternate.

462
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:09,301
You're all so talented

463
00:21:09,301 --> 00:21:11,604
I know Card Capital
will be well represented

464
00:21:11,604 --> 00:21:12,838
in the weeks to come.

465
00:21:12,838 --> 00:21:14,240
Everyone, please.

466
00:21:14,240 --> 00:21:16,942
Give these four players a
great big round of applause!

467
00:21:16,942 --> 00:21:19,879
(applause)

468
00:21:22,448 --> 00:21:23,048
You did it!

469
00:21:23,048 --> 00:21:24,116
That's awesome.

470
00:21:24,116 --> 00:21:26,252
You guys rock!

471
00:21:26,252 --> 00:21:29,789
It's great, isn't it?

472
00:21:29,789 --> 00:21:32,758
Hey, Aichi!

473
00:21:32,758 --> 00:21:34,493
Can you believe this?

474
00:21:34,493 --> 00:21:36,495
We're going to the
Regional Championship, bro!

475
00:21:36,495 --> 00:21:37,596
We're gonna get the chance

476
00:21:37,596 --> 00:21:39,832
to play against so
many great players!

477
00:21:39,832 --> 00:21:41,934
All right, I can't
wait to get out there

478
00:21:41,934 --> 00:21:44,136
and show everyone in
the world what we've got.

479
00:21:44,136 --> 00:21:45,938
‐Say what?
‐Say what?

480
00:21:45,938 --> 00:21:47,339
What we've got.

481
00:21:47,339 --> 00:21:49,408
Emi, please watch me!

482
00:21:49,408 --> 00:21:51,610
First we're gonna win
regional qualifier,

483
00:21:51,610 --> 00:21:54,079
and then it's off to
the National Championship.

484
00:21:54,079 --> 00:21:57,349
After that we can
g‐, g‐, g‐, go...

485
00:21:59,485 --> 00:22:00,786
Let's go!

486
00:22:00,786 --> 00:22:03,355
Oh, yeah, I'm all fired up.

487
00:22:03,355 --> 00:22:05,291
♪

488
00:22:05,291 --> 00:22:06,725
Wait.

489
00:22:06,725 --> 00:22:09,995
So I'll be on the same team
as Kamui, Misaki, and Kai?

490
00:22:09,995 --> 00:22:11,797
At the Vanguard Championships?

491
00:22:11,797 --> 00:22:13,432
In front of all those strangers?

492
00:22:13,432 --> 00:22:15,234
(crowd cheering)

493
00:22:15,234 --> 00:22:17,036
Huh?

494
00:22:17,036 --> 00:22:20,206
I wonder if I'm
imagining this right.

495
00:22:20,206 --> 00:22:23,275
Huh, a baseball?

496
00:22:26,679 --> 00:23:56,001
♪

497
00:24:00,839 --> 00:24:02,708
I'm gonna be in a regional
Vanguard tournament?

498
00:24:02,708 --> 00:24:04,109
Yes.

499
00:24:04,109 --> 00:24:07,313
Our four semi finalists are
moving on to bigger things.

500
00:24:07,313 --> 00:24:08,380
Make me proud!

501
00:24:08,380 --> 00:24:09,548
Right.

502
00:24:09,548 --> 00:24:11,417
There's a little
time before regionals.

503
00:24:11,417 --> 00:24:13,385
Devote your time to training.

504
00:24:13,385 --> 00:24:16,655
Yeah, only I'm not
sure how to get better.

505
00:24:16,655 --> 00:24:18,691
Next time, the fearsome undead.

506
00:24:18,691 --> 00:24:20,793
The granblue deck.

507
00:24:20,793 --> 00:24:22,528
This person is really good.

508
00:24:22,528 --> 00:24:24,330
Oh, another shop?

509
00:24:24,330 --> 00:24:25,965
You're leaving Card Capital?

510
00:24:25,965 --> 00:24:28,167
For another shop?

